    If no options are specified, ffiinnggeerr(1) defaults to the --ll style output if
    operands are provided, otherwise to the --ss style. Some fields may be
    missing, in either format, if information is not available for them.

    If no arguments are specified, ffiinnggeerr(1) will print an entry for each user
